summary: This code reads a log file named "standard_pattern.log", removes empty lines and non-blank lines, stores the remaining pattern in a list named 'fuck0', and prints it out.

details.comment: This code reads a log file named "standard_pattern.log", removes empty lines and non-blank lines, stores the remaining pattern in a list named 'fuck0', and prints it out.
details.content:
# Keep the pattern inside a list.
with open("standard_pattern.log","r") as fuck:
    fuck0=list(filter((lambda x:x!=""),fuck.read().split("\n")))
    print(fuck0)
